      <h2>Changes</h2>
      <p>We may update these Terms from time to time. The “last updated” date above reflects the current version, and continued use of the Site means you accept the updated Terms.</p>

      <h2>Governing law</h2>
      <p>These Terms are governed by the laws of <strong>[your jurisdiction]</strong>, without regard to its conflict-of-laws rules.</p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>Questions? Email <a href={`mailto:${site.contactEmail}`}>{site.contactEmail}</a>.</p>

      <p class="note">This is a generic starter document provided for convenience and is not legal advice. Replace “[your jurisdiction]” and have it reviewed and tailored by qualified counsel before relying on it.</p>
    </article>
  </div>
</Base>
